{
  "texts": [
    "It demonstrated the effectiveness of pre-training followed by fine-tuning on a wide range of NLP benchmarks, leading to remarkable improvements in various NLP applications such as sentiment analysis, question answering and machine translation; RoBERTa [45] is an advancement over the BERT model and improves its performance through several key modifications in its pre-training procedure.",
    "Notable changes include the utilization of an expansive and diverse training corpus, enabling processing of longer input sequences, employing larger batch sizes, elimination of the Next Sentence Prediction (NSP) task, careful fine-tuning of training parameters and a departure from discriminative masking during pre-training.",
    "These two studies, especially BERT, are the most representative works in the field of PLM.",
    "These works have inspired a wealth of subsequent research and established the \"pre-training followed by fine-tuning\" learning paradigm.",
    "Following the principles of this paradigm, numerous PLMs have been proposed, typically involving enhancements in either model architecture [15,46,47] or pre-training objectives [48][49][50].Based on PLMs, researchers have observed that increasing the scale of PLM, whether by enlarging the model size or the amount of training data, frequently results in enhanced model capability for downstream tasks."
  ]
}